parameters.name: filterCriteria
parameters.description: Details on the filters to apply to your finding results. awsAccountId (list) --- Details of the Amazon Web Services account IDs used to filter findings. (dict) --- An object that describes the details of a string filter. The operator to use when comparing values in the filter. The value to filter on. codeVulnerabilityDetectorName (list) --- The name of the detector used to identify a code vulnerability in a Lambda function used to filter findings. codeVulnerabilityDetectorTags (list) --- The detector type tag associated with the vulnerability used to filter findings. Detector tags group related vulnerabilities by common themes or tactics. For a list of available tags by programming language, see Java tags, or Python tags. codeVulnerabilityFilePath (list) --- The file path to the file in a Lambda function that contains a code vulnerability used to filter findings. componentId (list) --- Details of the component IDs used to filter findings. componentType (list) --- Details of the component types used to filter findings. ec2InstanceImageId (list) --- Details of the Amazon EC2 instance image IDs used to filter findings. ec2InstanceSubnetId (list) --- Details of the Amazon EC2 instance subnet IDs used to filter findings. ec2InstanceVpcId (list) --- Details of the Amazon EC2 instance VPC IDs used to filter findings. ecrImageArchitecture (list) --- Details of the Amazon ECR image architecture types used to filter findings. ecrImageHash (list) --- Details of the Amazon ECR image hashes used to filter findings. ecrImagePushedAt (list) --- Details on the Amazon ECR image push date and time used to filter findings. (dict) --- Contains details on the time range used to filter findings. endInclusive (datetime) --- A timestamp representing the end of the time period filtered on. startInclusive (datetime) --- A timestamp representing the start of the time period filtered on. ecrImageRegistry (list) --- Details on the Amazon ECR registry used to filter findings. ecrImageRepositoryName (list) --- Details on the name of the Amazon ECR repository used to filter findings. ecrImageTags (list) --- The tags attached to the Amazon ECR container image. epssScore (list) --- The EPSS score used to filter findings. (dict) --- An object that describes the details of a number filter. lowerInclusive (float) --- The lowest number to be included in the filter. upperInclusive (float) --- The highest number to be included in the filter. exploitAvailable (list) --- Filters the list of Amazon Web Services Lambda findings by the availability of exploits. findingArn (list) --- Details on the finding ARNs used to filter findings. findingStatus (list) --- Details on the finding status types used to filter findings. findingType (list) --- Details on the finding types used to filter findings. firstObservedAt (list) --- Details on the date and time a finding was first seen used to filter findings. fixAvailable (list) --- Details on whether a fix is available through a version update. This value can be YES, NO, or PARTIAL. A PARTIAL fix means that some, but not all, of the packages identified in the finding have fixes available through updated versions. inspectorScore (list) --- The Amazon Inspector score to filter on. lambdaFunctionExecutionRoleArn (list) --- Filters the list of Amazon Web Services Lambda functions by execution role. lambdaFunctionLastModifiedAt (list) --- Filters the list of Amazon Web Services Lambda functions by the date and time that a user last updated the configuration, in ISO 8601 format (dict) --- Contains details on the time range used to filter findings. lambdaFunctionLayers (list) --- Filters the list of Amazon Web Services Lambda functions by the function's layers. A Lambda function can have up to five layers. lambdaFunctionName (list) --- Filters the list of Amazon Web Services Lambda functions by the name of the function. lambdaFunctionRuntime (list) --- Filters the list of Amazon Web Services Lambda functions by the runtime environment for the Lambda function. lastObservedAt (list) --- Details on the date and time a finding was last seen used to filter findings. networkProtocol (list) --- Details on network protocol used to filter findings. portRange (list) --- Details on the port ranges used to filter findings. (dict) --- An object that describes the details of a port range filter. beginInclusive (integer) --- The port number the port range begins at. endInclusive (integer) --- The port number the port range ends at. relatedVulnerabilities (list) --- Details on the related vulnerabilities used to filter findings. resourceId (list) --- Details on the resource IDs used to filter findings. resourceTags (list) --- Details on the resource tags used to filter findings. (dict) --- An object that describes details of a map filter. The tag key used in the filter. value (string) --- The tag value used in the filter. resourceType (list) --- Details on the resource types used to filter findings. severity (list) --- Details on the severity used to filter findings. title (list) --- Details on the finding title used to filter findings. updatedAt (list) --- Details on the date and time a finding was last updated at used to filter findings. vendorSeverity (list) --- Details on the vendor severity used to filter findings. vulnerabilityId (list) --- Details on the vulnerability ID used to filter findings. vulnerabilitySource (list) --- Details on the vulnerability type used to filter findings. vulnerablePackages (list) --- Details on the vulnerable packages used to filter findings. (dict) --- Contains information on the details of a package filter. architecture (dict) --- An object that contains details on the package architecture type to filter on. epoch (dict) --- An object that contains details on the package epoch to filter on. filePath (dict) --- An object that contains details on the package file path to filter on. name (dict) --- An object that contains details on the name of the package to filter on. release (dict) --- An object that contains details on the package release to filter on. sourceLambdaLayerArn (dict) --- An object that describes the details of a string filter. sourceLayerHash (dict) --- An object that contains details on the source layer hash to filter on. version (dict) --- The package version to filter on. The value to filter on.

nested_items.description: Details about the code vulnerability identified in a Lambda function used to filter findings.

nested_items.description: The Common Weakness Enumeration (CWE) item associated with the detected vulnerability.
(string) ---

nested_items.description: The ID for the Amazon CodeGuru detector associated with the finding. For more information on detectors see Amazon CodeGuru Detector Library.

nested_items.description: The name of the detector used to identify the code vulnerability. For more information on detectors see CodeGuru Detector Library.

nested_items.name: resources
nested_items.description: Contains information on the resources involved in a finding. The resource value determines the valid values for type in your request. For more information, see Finding types in the Amazon Inspector user guide.

nested_items.name: awsEc2Instance
nested_items.description: An object that contains details about the Amazon EC2 instance involved in the finding.

nested_items.name: iamInstanceProfileArn
nested_items.description: The IAM instance profile ARN of the Amazon EC2 instance.

nested_items.name: imageId
nested_items.description: The image ID of the Amazon EC2 instance.

nested_items.name: ipV4Addresses
nested_items.description: The IPv4 addresses of the Amazon EC2 instance.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: ipV6Addresses
nested_items.description: The IPv6 addresses of the Amazon EC2 instance.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: keyName
nested_items.description: The name of the key pair used to launch the Amazon EC2 instance.

nested_items.name: launchedAt
nested_items.description: The date and time the Amazon EC2 instance was launched at.

nested_items.name: platform
nested_items.description: The platform of the Amazon EC2 instance.

nested_items.name: subnetId
nested_items.description: The subnet ID of the Amazon EC2 instance.

nested_items.name: type
nested_items.description: The type of the Amazon EC2 instance.

nested_items.name: vpcId
nested_items.description: The VPC ID of the Amazon EC2 instance.

nested_items.name: awsEcrContainerImage
nested_items.description: An object that contains details about the Amazon ECR container image involved in the finding.

nested_items.name: architecture
nested_items.description: The architecture of the Amazon ECR container image.

nested_items.name: author
nested_items.description: The image author of the Amazon ECR container image.

nested_items.name: imageHash
nested_items.description: The image hash of the Amazon ECR container image.

nested_items.name: imageTags
nested_items.description: The image tags attached to the Amazon ECR container image.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: platform
nested_items.description: The platform of the Amazon ECR container image.

nested_items.name: pushedAt
nested_items.description: The date and time the Amazon ECR container image was pushed.

nested_items.name: registry
nested_items.description: The registry for the Amazon ECR container image.

nested_items.name: repositoryName
nested_items.description: The name of the repository the Amazon ECR container image resides in.

nested_items.name: awsLambdaFunction
nested_items.description: A summary of the information about an Amazon Web Services Lambda function affected by a finding.

nested_items.name: architectures
nested_items.description: The instruction set architecture that the Amazon Web Services Lambda function supports. Architecture is a string array with one of the valid values. The default architecture value is x86_64.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: codeSha256
nested_items.description: The SHA256 hash of the Amazon Web Services Lambda function's deployment package.

nested_items.name: executionRoleArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Web Services Lambda function's execution role.

nested_items.name: functionName
nested_items.description: The name of the Amazon Web Services Lambda function.

nested_items.name: lastModifiedAt
nested_items.description: The date and time that a user last updated the configuration, in ISO 8601 format.

nested_items.name: layers
nested_items.description: The Amazon Web Services Lambda function's layers. A Lambda function can have up to five layers.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: packageType
nested_items.description: The type of deployment package. Set to Image for container image and set Zip for .zip file archive.

nested_items.name: runtime
nested_items.description: The runtime environment for the Amazon Web Services Lambda function.

nested_items.name: version
nested_items.description: The version of the Amazon Web Services Lambda function.

nested_items.name: vpcConfig
nested_items.description: The Amazon Web Services Lambda function's networking configuration.

nested_items.name: securityGroupIds
nested_items.description: The VPC security groups and subnets that are attached to an Amazon Web Services Lambda function. For more information, see VPC Settings.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: subnetIds
nested_items.description: A list of VPC subnet IDs.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: vpcId
nested_items.description: The ID of the VPC.

nested_items.name: id
nested_items.description: The ID of the resource.

nested_items.name: partition
nested_items.description: The partition of the resource.

nested_items.name: region
nested_items.description: The Amazon Web Services Region the impacted resource is located in.
(string) ---
(string) ---

nested_items.name: type
nested_items.description: The type of resource.

nested_items.name: severity
nested_items.description: The severity of the finding. UNTRIAGED applies to PACKAGE_VULNERABILITY type findings that the vendor has not assigned a severity yet. For more information, see Severity levels for findings in the Amazon Inspector user guide.

nested_items.name: status
nested_items.description: The status of the finding.

nested_items.name: title
nested_items.description: The title of the finding.

nested_items.name: type
nested_items.description: The type of the finding. The type value determines the valid values for resource in your request. For more information, see Finding types in the Amazon Inspector user guide.

nested_items.name: updatedAt
nested_items.description: The date and time the finding was last updated at.

nested_items.name: nextToken
nested_items.description: A token to use for paginating results that are returned in the response. Set the value of this parameter to null for the first request to a list action. For subsequent calls, use the NextToken value returned from the previous request to continue listing results after the first page.
